procedures.name: Blood Draw

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, and pregnancy tests.

procedures.name: Physical Examination

code.decode: Office or other outpatient visit for the evaluation and management of an established patient

procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems. Symptom-driven physical examinations may also be performed.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Urine Collection

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent for bilirubin, glucose, hemoglobin, ketones, leukocytes, nitrite, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, any number of these constituents; non-automated, with microscopy

procedures.label: Urine Sample
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screen, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour collection for copper and molybdenum measurement.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sample
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples to measure copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Oral Administration of ALXN1840
procedures.label: Drug Administration
procedures.description: Participant self-administration of ALXN1840 tablets with 240 mL of water on an empty stomach.

procedures.name: Medical History Collection
procedures.label: Medical History
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, demographics, Wilson disease history, and prior treatment information.

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing monitoring and collection of information on adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Cannula Placement

code.decode: Introduction of needle or intracatheter, vein

procedures.label: Cannulation
procedures.description: Placement of a cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen

code.decode: Drug test(s), presumptive, any number of drug classes, any number of devices or procedures; capable of being read by direct optical observation only (eg, dipsticks, cups, cards, cartridges) includes sample validation when performed, per date of service

procedures.label: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.description: Screening test to detect the presence of drugs in urine.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test

code.decode: Urine pregnancy test, by visual color comparison methods

procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum pregnancy test for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Height, Weight, and BMI Measurement
procedures.label: Anthropometrics
procedures.description: Measurement of participant height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: Venous Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: Venous Catheter
medicalDevices.description: A catheter may be used for venous access for blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Analytical instrument used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
